  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Inteliquent**, a prominent telecommunications services provider, actively recruits new graduates from a variety of universities across the United States. While specific recruitment partners or target universities can vary over time based on company needs and recruitment strategies, Inteliquent typically looks for talent from institutions known for strong programs in relevant fields.\n\n### **Common Universities Inteliquent May Recruit From:**\nWhile Inteliquent may not publicly disclose an exhaustive list of target universities, they often recruit from universities with robust programs in technology, business, engineering, and communications. Some examples might include:\n\n- **Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)**\n- **Stanford University**\n- **University of California, Berkeley**\n- **Carnegie Mellon University**\n- **University of Texas at Austin**\n- **Georgia Institute of Technology**\n- **University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign**\n- **Purdue University**\n- **New York University (NYU)**\n- **University of Southern California (USC)**\n\n*Note:* This list is not specific to Inteliquent but represents universities with strong programs that align with the skills typically sought by telecommunications companies.\n\n### **Preferred Majors and Areas of Study:**\nInteliquent looks for graduates with backgrounds that support their business operations and innovation in telecommunications. Common majors and fields of study include:\n\n1. **Computer Science & Information Technology:**\n   - Software Development\n   - Network Engineering\n   - Cybersecurity\n   - Data Science and Analytics\n\n2. **Telecommunications:**\n   - Telecommunications Engineering\n   - Network Communications\n\n3. **Engineering:**\n   - Electrical Engineering\n   - Systems Engineering\n\n4. **Business Administration & Management:**\n   - Business Operations\n   - Marketing\n   - Finance\n   - Human Resources\n\n5. **Marketing and Communications:**\n   - Digital Marketing\n   - Public Relations\n\n6. **Data Analytics and Statistics:**\n   - Data Analysis\n   - Business Intelligence\n\n7. **Sales and Customer Service:**\n   - Sales Management\n   - Customer Relationship Management\n\n8. **Project Management:**\n   - Project Coordination\n   - Operations Management\n\n### **How to Enhance Your Chances:**\n\n- **Internships:** Gaining relevant internship experience in telecommunications or related fields can make your application stand out.\n  \n- **Campus Recruitment Events:** Participate in job fairs and recruitment events hosted by Inteliquent or industry-related organizations at your university.\n  \n- **Professional Networking:** Connect with current Inteliquent employees on platforms like LinkedIn to learn more about opportunities and gain referrals.\n  \n- **Skill Development:** Acquire skills relevant to the roles you\u2019re interested in, such as proficiency in specific software, programming languages, or telecommunications technologies.\n\n### **Next Steps:**\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information on Inteliquent\u2019s recruitment practices, including specific target universities and desired qualifications, consider the following actions:\n\n- **Visit the [Inteliquent Careers Page](https://www.inteliquent.com/company/careers):** Here you can find current job openings, internship opportunities, and detailed descriptions of roles and requirements.\n\n- **Contact HR or Recruitment Teams:** Reach out directly through provided contact information on their website for specific inquiries.\n\n- **Attend Career Fairs:** Look for events where Inteliquent is participating to engage directly with their recruitment representatives.\n\n- **Follow Inteliquent on Professional Networks:** Platforms like LinkedIn often have updates on job postings and company news that can provide insights into their hiring trends.\n\nBy aligning your academic background and skills with Inteliquent\u2019s needs and actively engaging with their recruitment channels, you can enhance your prospects of securing a position as a new graduate.",
